This article is about Executive Order 13550, which establishes the Pakistan and Afghanistan Support Office (PASO) within the Department of State. The purpose of PASO is to support executive departments and agencies in strengthening the governments of Afghanistan and Pakistan, enhancing their capacity to resist extremists, and maintaining a U.S. diplomatic presence in both countries. PASO will assume the functions of the Afghanistan Support Office and perform other functions as assigned by the Secretary of State. The PASO will be headed by a Director appointed by the Secretary and will be based in Washington, D.C., Pakistan, and Afghanistan. The order also includes general provisions and specifies that PASO will terminate at the end of the maximum period permitted by law, unless sooner terminated by the Secretary.